From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 19:55:13 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(cli): add runs prune subcommand for safe cleanup of old
 runs (FR-E83)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

`flowai-workflow runs prune [--workflow <dir>] --keep <N> [--dry-run]`
deletes the oldest run directories under `<workflow>/runs/`, keeping
the N newest deletable runs. Hard safety rules: non-terminal replayed
journal status, the run referenced by runs/.lock, and runs with a
missing/unreplayable journal.jsonl are never deleted — reported as
skipped with a reason and excluded from the --keep budget. Bad --keep
(anything but a non-negative integer) → clear error + non-zero exit.

- src/state/prune.ts: pruneRuns selection/execution, reusing
  getRunDir/getRunsRoot, the journal replayer, and lock helpers.
- src/state/state.ts: getRunsRoot single-source path helper.
- src/state/run-journal.ts: export isTerminalRunStatus (was private).
- src/cli.ts: parseRunsPruneArgs + runRunsPrune + `runs` dispatch +
  --help coverage.
- Tests: src/state/prune_test.ts (10 temp-dir fixture cases),
  src/cli_test.ts (FR-E83 parser cases).
- SRS: FR-E83 section; FR-E70/71/72 moved verbatim to new
  06b-plugin-distribution.md to keep section files under the docs
  token budget; indexes repointed.
- SDS + README synced; task documents/tasks/2026/06/runs-prune.md.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
