+## Solution
+
+Selected variant: **B — dedicated `src/state/prune.ts` module + thin CLI
+wiring** (see variant analysis in the session log; quick-fix inline-in-cli
+rejected for testability, command-registry/MCP exposure rejected as
+out-of-scope investment).
+
+1. **Export terminal-status helper (RED → GREEN).**
+   - `src/state/run-journal.ts`: export the existing private
+     `isTerminalStatus(status: RunState["status"]): boolean` as
+     `isTerminalRunStatus` with JSDoc (JSR slow-types require explicit
+     types). No behaviour change.
+
+2. **`src/state/prune.ts` — selection + execution (RED → GREEN).**
+   - Types (all exported with JSDoc):
+     ```ts
+     interface PruneRunInfo { run_id: string; started_at?: string; status?: RunState["status"] }
+     interface PruneSkip extends PruneRunInfo { reason: string }
+     interface PruneResult { deleted: PruneRunInfo[]; kept: PruneRunInfo[]; skipped: PruneSkip[]; dry_run: boolean }
+     async function pruneRuns(opts: { workflowDir: string; keep: number; dryRun?: boolean }): Promise<PruneResult>
+     ```
+   - Validate `keep` defensively (`Number.isInteger(keep) && keep >= 0`,
+     else throw) — CLI parsing is the primary gate, this is fail-fast.
+   - Read lock once: `readLockInfo(defaultLockPath(workflowDir))`;
+     `NotFound`/`SyntaxError` → no locked run id; other errors rethrow.
+   - Enumerate directory entries of `<workflowDir>/runs/`
+     (`Deno.readDir`); missing `runs/` → empty result. Only
+     `isDirectory` entries are run candidates; each maps to
+     `getRunDir(entry.name, workflowDir)`.
+   - Classify each run:
+     - lock-referenced → skipped `referenced by runs/.lock`;
+     - `loadStateFromJournal` throws `NotFound` → skipped
+       `journal.jsonl missing — state unknown, kept`;
+     - throws anything else → skipped
+       `journal replay failed (<message>) — state unknown, kept`;
+     - replayed status non-terminal → skipped
+       `non-terminal status: <status>`;
+     - else deletable, with `started_at` + `status` from the replay.
+   - Sort deletable newest-first (`started_at` desc, run_id desc
+     tie-break); first `keep` → `kept`; rest → `deleted`.
+   - Unless `dryRun`, `Deno.remove(runDir, { recursive: true })` each
+     deleted dir. Deletion errors are NOT swallowed (fail fast).
+   - No engine/workflow coupling: module knows nothing about node
+     names or workflow structure (engine-workflow separation).
+
+3. **Tests `src/state/prune_test.ts` (RED first).**
+   - Fixture helper: `makeRun(workflowDir, runId, {startedAt, terminal})`
+     → `RunJournalWriter.open(getRunDir(...))`, append engine-shaped
