+     `run_completed`/`run_failed` events (mirrors
+     `lifecycle-replay_test.ts::appendRunStart`).
+   - Cases: keeps N newest / deletes oldest; non-terminal skipped even
+     when oldest; locked terminal run skipped (write
+     `runs/.lock` JSON via the `LockInfo` shape); missing journal
+     skipped; malformed journal skipped; `keep: 0` deletes all
+     terminal unlocked; `dryRun: true` reports would-delete and leaves
+     directories on disk; negative/non-integer `keep` throws. Every
+     deletion/retention assertion checks the REAL filesystem state
+     (`Deno.stat` on the run dirs), not just the returned report.
+
+4. **CLI wiring (RED via `cli_test.ts`, then GREEN).**
+   - `src/cli.ts`: export `parseRunsPruneArgs(args: string[]):
+     { workflowDir?: string; keep: number; dryRun: boolean }` —
+     hand-rolled loop, `--workflow`/`--workflow=`, `--keep`/`--keep=`,
+     `--dry-run`; unknown arg → throw; missing/invalid `--keep` →
+     `Invalid --keep value: <raw>. Expected non-negative integer.`
+     (integer-string check, no float/NaN acceptance).
+   - `runRunsPrune(args)` handler: resolve workflow
+     (explicit `--workflow` → else `resolveActiveWorkflow`, error when
+     null, mirroring `runAnswer`), normalized via
