+     `pruneRuns`; print per-run
+     lines (`deleted <id>`, `kept <id>`, `skipped <id> — <reason>`,
+     with `would delete` under `--dry-run`) + summary line
+     `Pruned: <D> deleted, <K> kept, <S> skipped.`; exit 0 on success,
+     `Error: <msg>` + exit 1 on failure.
+   - Dispatch in `import.meta.main`: `if (subcommand === "runs")` —
+     second positional must be `prune`, else error + usage + exit 1.
+   - `printUsage`: add `flowai-workflow runs prune --workflow <dir> --keep <N> [--dry-run]`
+     usage line, `runs prune` subcommand bullet, and an example.
+   - `cli_test.ts`: `FR-E83 parseRunsPruneArgs` tests — happy path,
+     `=`-forms, `--dry-run`, missing `--keep`, `-1`, `1.5`, `abc`,
+     unknown-arg rejection.
+
+5. **SRS + docs (same commit).**
+   - `documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md`:
