+## Follow-ups
+
+- `runs list` / inspection output — explicitly out of scope here.
+- Exposing prune through the MCP command layer (`src/mcp/commands.ts`)
+  if plugin hosts need programmatic cleanup — deferred until a host
+  asks for it.
+- Age-based pruning (`--older-than <duration>`) — deferred; `--keep N`
+  is the only requested policy.
+- Lock-read vs run-start race: a run starting between the lock read
+  and deletion is theoretically unprotected by the lock rule alone,
+  but its journal replays as non-terminal, so the status rule still
+  protects it. Accepted residual risk for a manual housekeeping CLI;
+  revisit only if prune becomes automated/long-running.
